social_posts.post_text: 2 years being loved by you & I’d choose it again in every lifetime if it meant I got to feel your love. I love you more every day, Keith. To the moon & back forever. 🧡🕊🌙

Keith,

31.5 million seconds. 525,000 minutes. 365 days. I didn’t want to live any of those without you - but I did. 

I want to say I don’t know how I did it - but I do. Our loving & loyal friends and family, game nights, therapy, TTL, the grief community, my Instagram friends, and the biggest of all - your undying love. 

I still pinch myself every day. I still wake up in a panic looking for you on the other side of the bed. Grief doesn’t go away. Missing you will never go away. My unconditional love for you will never go away. 

Keith, I vowed this to you then and I vow this to you now. I will love, respect, adore, and dedicate myself to you for eternity. I love you with my entire being. Thank you for being you. Thank you for loving me the way you do. I love you to the moon and back forever. 🧡
FOR KEITH 🧡🧡🧡

To the man who wanted to be a father so badly, I miss you more than I can conjure up. I hate that you’re not here. I had no clue today would hit me like it did, but that’s grief in a whole - it blindsides you when you’re least expecting it. I wish we got to live out the life we dreamt of for longer than we did. I wish you were here longer & I know a lifetime with you still wouldn’t be enough. 💔 

I love you to the moon & BACK forever. 🧡

18 months. A year and a half since the world saw you smile. 

Grief is so strange. It’s ever-changing. It evolves, destroys, grows, devastates and everything in between. It affects every single aspect of your life. 

It’s also extremely confusing. 

All I know for certain is, I love you more today than I have ever loved you before. You continue to love and guide me & I feel it every day. I’ve learned that love grows & evolves whether your person is here or not. 

Love never stops. There is no end to it. How beautiful is that?

I love you Keith 🧡 WYWH

Woah... I can’t believe this is my life. All of it - the good, the bad, the ugly. The ups, the downs, the highs & the lows. This is not one bit how I envisioned my life to go. 

I’ve learned so much since March 26th 2022. Through the heartbreak, I’ve learned that I’m happy to be here. I’m happy to be gifted enough to help others. I’m happy I can help support grievers even if it’s .001%. Don’t get me wrong: I don’t wish this on anyone! I’m not happy this happened to me. I didn’t need this to happen to become a “better person”, more self aware, more helpful. But it happened. 💔 I’m not happy this happened, but I’m proud of who I’ve become after tragedy.

Grief is confusing. There are so many mixed emotions, but one thing is clear - LOVE is everything. 🫶🏼🧡 I wouldn’t be here today if it wasn’t for love. 

#FortheloveofKeith #TTL #GriefSucks

New Years is hard for grievers. We understand the concept of time - it comes and goes and doesn’t wait for ANYONE or anything. We want time to stop. We want time to rewind. And we also know that’s impossible (we’ve tried)… 

As I reflect on 2023 - I give myself grace. I wanted time to stop & then I came to an acceptance that it couldn’t. I started to live forward rather than back. I started to look at a future instead of a past. I started to live for the now & not for the then. 

Living forward doesn’t mean I didn’t also live the past. It’s scarred into me for life. It doesn’t mean I forgot. It doesn’t mean I stopped loving. But it means I took a step forward, towards growth, love, life. 

None of this would be made possible without the people who loved me through my darkness, pain, growth, grief. I wouldn’t be here without any of you! 

Thank you for existing. Thank you for being here. Thank you for being YOU! 

Here’s what I’m giving to 2024 🧡
- Less judgment, more kindness
- Living in every moment
- Gratitude for what I have 
- A life worth living 
- Love that is greater than anything 
- Appreciation for the things around me
- Continued focus on my health & wellness
- Living each day for those who can’t

I have no words. Holding someone you love dead in your hands changes you. Grief changes you. Your perspective on life is altered forever. I am so proud of how far I’ve come. I am so honored to be standing here, to live and love as hard as I can. I am so thankful for those that choose me every day - I can’t thank them enough. 🫶🏼🧡
